paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
crimes_file = sc.textFile('file:///root/crimes.csv')
header = crimes_file.filter(lambda x: 'MI_PRINX' in x).map(lambda x: [x.strip().replace(' ', '_') for x in x.split(',')])
crimes = crimes_file.filter(lambda x: 'MI_PRINX' not in x) \
 .map(lambda x: [x.strip() for x in x.split(',')])

sqlContext.registerDataFrameAsTable(sqlContext.createDataFrame(crimes, header.collect()[0]), 'crimes')
%sql select * from crimes where beat = '605' and lower(location) like '%berne%'

%sql 
select
 neighborhood,
 regexp_extract(trim(split(rpt_date, "\/")[0]), "0*([1-9][0-9]*|0)", 1) as month,
 count(*) as count
from crimes
group by neighborhood, regexp_extract(trim(split(rpt_date, "\/")[0]), "0*([1-9][0-9]*|0)", 1)
